{
  "stem": "4361.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Just from one day to another, he had to give the keys to his business.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they did the same thing with all the other businessmen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Eventually-- this is in March, end of March-- eventually they forbade professionals-- doctors, lawyers-- to practice.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But what I remember with a great deal of sorrow is how my father, who was still a young man-- not to me in those days, but he was in his early 50s.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "At the most, he was 53, 54 years old-- that this tall man suddenly became humped.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean, he just collapsed, because he had no-- I mean-- I remember seeing him in the morning getting dressed, and he was always so dapper with the monogrammed shirt and-- and his pants being-- the crease, you know?",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We use to-- we use to joke about it that the fly on my father's-- the crease of my father's pants would commit suicide if he--",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this man-- and he was so fastidious, and he was just wonderful.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was still fastidious, but he was a broken man.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that broke my heart very much.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother, who was a very strong woman, very strong woman-- even though the death of her oldest child had broken her, and-- and-- and she stayed away from music and from many things-- but she said it's all right.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was a great believer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She said, God will help us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We'll overcome this, too.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And sort of Passover was approaching, and she said, well, God took us out from Egypt, from Israel.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Things will be all right.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I do remember my father.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was just a broken man.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Just a broken man.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I am afraid it was around that time that I said to him, your Hungarians, Daddy.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
